  "lastCommit": {
    "hash": "aa9f85c",
    "message": "fix: iPhone category grid scroll + name truncation\n\n- Add overscroll-y-contain and WebkitOverflowScrolling for iOS Safari\n- Switch from truncate to line-clamp-2 so full category names display\n- Increase tile min-height from 64px to 72px to accommodate two lines\n- Reduce heading size to reclaim vertical space\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
    "branch": "feature/phone-category-scroll-fix",
    "date": "2026-03-15"
  },
  "recentCommits": [
    {
      "hash": "aa9f85c",
      "message": "fix: iPhone category grid scroll + name truncation\n\n- Add overscroll-y-contain and WebkitOverflowScrolling for iOS Safari\n- Switch from truncate to line-clamp-2 so full category names display\n- Increase tile min-height from 64px to 72px to accommodate two lines\n- Reduce heading size to reclaim vertical space\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "feature/phone-category-scroll-fix",
      "date": "2026-03-15"
    },
    {
      "hash": "3b61d6e",
      "message": "fix: PWA lock screen verifies PINs against DB instead of hardcoded array\n\nPwaLockScreen was checking PINs against DEMO_STAFF in staff-pins.ts,\nso real staff PINs from the database were rejected. Now calls\nPOST /api/pwa/staff/verify-pin first, falls back to local demo staff\nonly when the API is unreachable (offline mode).\n\n- switchUser() is now async, calls pwaApi.verifyPin(pin)\n- API response (display_name, role) mapped to PwaStaffMember shape\n- Verified user cached in localStorage for fast restore on reload\n- Loading state shown while API call is in flight\n- PIN pad disabled during verification to prevent double-submit\n- Role normalization: gm→manager, host→server, etc.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "fix/pwa-auth-api-verify-pin",
      "date": "2026-03-15"
    },
    {
      "hash": "5e69060",
      "message": "fix: iPad order entry layout — wider menu panel, wrapping categories, server name\n\n1. Column split changed from 55/45 to 65/35 — menu panel gets more\n   space, order summary panel is tighter (was mostly empty space)\n2. Category pills now flex-wrap instead of horizontal scroll — all\n   categories visible without scrolling at 1024x768\n3. Header shows server name from order (resolved from PIN→staff name)\n   instead of only the elapsed timer\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "fix/tablet-order-entry-layout",
      "date": "2026-03-15"
    },
    {
      "hash": "f7b503c",
      "message": "chore: add build tag to QuickSwitchBar for cache busting",
